Attempting to map tags in old master branch to commits within new master branch

https://www.git-scm.com/docs/git-log#_pretty_formats

```console
$ git log "--pretty=format:%s %at" | wc -l
1728
$ git log "--pretty=format:%s %at" | sort | uniq | wc -l
1728
```

From the above log output number of lines matching when sorted and made unique we know that we can reliably look up based on commit message plus timestamp to map from one history to the other.

The `0.4.0` tag is special because it got updated from the `0.4.x` branch...

```console
$ tag=0.3.0; commit_subject_unixtime=$(git log -n 1 "--pretty=format:%s %at" $tag);
$ git log "--pretty=format:%H %s %at" | grep "${commit_subject_unixtime}"
9587a423a0d535198f7ccf6c2726525210bf1b0c df: Real DataFlows and HTTP MultiComm 1572122820
```

Remap all the tags by looking for the subject and time.

```console
$ for tag in $(git tag | grep -vE 'model|0.4.0'); do commit_subject_unixtime=$(git log -n 1 "--pretty=format:%s %at" $tag); git tag -f $tag $(git log "--pretty=format:%H %s %at" | grep "${commit_subject_unixtime}" | awk '{print $1}'); done
```
